The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter
PRESIDENT Mnangagwa is set to address the nation on the Covid-19 lockdown regulations tomorrow when the current level four lockdown measures expire at midnight. The address will be broadcast live across all media platforms at a time to be announced in the afternoon. According to a statement posted by the Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services this evening, the announcement will be made at a time to be advised in the afternoon. “His Excellency President @edmnangagwa will tomorrow,15 February 2021, make an announcement on the way forward as the two-week lockdown announced on January 29, 2021 expires. The address will be broadcast live on all national television, radio & social media platforms at a time to be advised in the afternoon,” read the statement.